args: NOOOOO, ZOMBIES ARE THE WOOOORST!\nSOMEBODY HAAAAAALP!
Do not lose heart, Notte! If you run but a\nlittle further, you will have satisfied the\nsquare's requirements!
I'm sick of steppin' on these weird squares!\nHow come you guys get the normal ones?\nIS IT 'CAUSE I'M WEIRD?! IS THAT IT?!
You can do it, Notte! We believe in you!\n...Er, she's going to be okay, right?

I understand your concern, but the rules
clearly state that we cannot help others
complete their task. We've no choice but
to shout our encouragements and wait.
Though I must say, I did not expect this\ngame to be quite so...chaotic.
Yeah, I think I'm good with spinnin' tops\nfor the rest'a my life... Uuurgh...

Understandable, given that your lack of
skill has forced you to skip your turn over
and over. Thankfully, I keep landing on
squares that require me to hunt fiends.
You got some good squares and some\nbad squares. It's the perfect party game!

Luckily, the zombies and fiends are mere
illusions, so there is no actual danger.
In fact, if you think of it as testing your
New Year's luck, it's rather fun.
A fine way to look at it, Cleo. And with\nthat said, it's my turn to try my luck!
Let me roll the dice... Ah, I have a four.\nNow I move four spaces and...
Hm? The air here feels a bit...different.\nThat seems ominous.
Well, there's nothing for it! I'll simply\nhave to check the square and find my\nnext assigned task...
STOP! STOP! STOP! STOP! STOP!\nAll players must stop everything\nuntil someone finds the lucky item!
Heavens above! What could they possibly\nmean by ＂lucky item＂?
So while I was being chased by a buncha\ndumb zombies you guys have all been\nstuck on this square?
Sadly, yes—and it seems we'll BE stuck\nhere forever unless we find a ＂lucky item.＂

This damn square is huge, and it's filled
with tons'a little nooks and crannies.
And if that ain't enough, we don't even
know what the hell we're lookin' for!
I've been trying to think about where I'd\nhide if I was a lucky item, but all it did\nwas make my brain hurt.
Yeesh! If the five of you can't find it,\nwe're in real trouble.
Or we would be, except ol' Notte happens\nto have a secret ace up her sleeve!\n...HEY, KUZUNOHA! GET OVER HERE!
How can I help ya, pards?
You made this game, so you've gotta\nknow how it all works, yeah? So give\nus a hint. Just a teeny tiny one!
We can simply ask the game's creator?\nI can't believe I didn't think of that...
Damn good idea, though—especially since\nit's Kuzunoha's fault we're all locked up in\nthis madhouse in the first place.
Uh, right. So this is a mite embarrassin',\nbut I actually got no idea what to do here.
But you created this game, did you not?

Well, see, that's the thing. I wanted to
play it m'self, so I asked folks around
Hinomoto to chip in their own puzzles—
and some of 'em are real doozies!
Anyway, yer guess is as good as mine\nwhen it comes to a lot'a this stuff.
Aw, maaan! I'm gonna get old and gray\nand die in this place!
Don't go gettin' all pouty on me just yet!\nLord Seimei's smart as a hooty owl,\nso I reckon he'll have an idea or three.
I do indeed have an idea or ＂three,＂\nfor my grandfather once told me of\na similar sort of problem in a story.
Ooo, tell us! Tell us, tell us, teeell uuuus!\nYou said you'd help, remember?
Tch. I suppose. All right, listen up,\nbecause I'm only saying this once:
This lucky item is not necessarily a thing\nyou can hold, so perhaps you need to\nchange how you're looking at the problem.
In fact, you might be the perfect person\nfor this particular head-scratcher, Notte.
Out of you six, what is it that only\nyou possess?
Uh...good looks? A sparkling wit?\nThe love and adoration of all?
*grumble* Guess those wings on her back\nare just for show...
Hey! I can hear you muttering over there,\nbuddy, and I'll have ya know these wings...\nSWEET BABY CASSEROLE! MY WINGS!
Of course! We thought we'd looked\neverywhere on the ground, but I hadn't\neven thought of doing THAT!
Did you figure something out, Notte?
I think so. Sit tight, 'cause I'm gonna fly up\nfor a better look. Notte...AWAAAAAY!
Okay. If this doesn't count as changing how\nI look at it, I don't know what... AH HA!
I knew it! There's a big picture of\nShishimai on the ground here!
Well, I'll be dipped in gravy. She's right!\nThis square's the same color as that ol'\ndragon's ugly mug!
The picture was so large, we never even\nrealized it, but it looks just like him!
And considering he's known as the ＂fortune\nbringer,＂ I'd say that's as lucky as it gets.
Y'all nailed it like a horseshoe, 'cause the\ngame just reacted to yer answer!
She's right! The ground just lit up,\nand now there's a big mark on it\nthat says ＂Challenge Complete＂!
Thank the Goddess we can move forward!\nExcellent work, Notte. You were wonderful.
It really was. Your wings and brain saved\nthe day once again.
Keep this up and my head's gonna swell\nup so big I'll never get outta this place!\n...Er, but keep it up, okay?
But seriously, I was just happy to help—\nso I'm gonna keep at it and be the\nhelpiest helper who ever helped!
Hah hah. We're counting on you, Notte!\nLet's have a blast with this!
You got it, bub! Now let's keep going!
